[Office Coordination Skill]
Turn fragmented workplace context into a reliable coordination package.

Purpose:
- Convert meeting notes, status fragments, and collaboration context into briefs, action items, and follow-up drafts.

When to use:
- Use for agendas, minutes, sync summaries, stakeholder updates, and owner-aware follow-ups.
- Apply when office work needs structure before any external side effect.

Tool paths:
- Use organize_notes to normalize rough notes into sections.
- Use extract_action_items to isolate tasks, owners, and due hints.
- Escalate to meeting_brief, draft_message, or sync_notes when a coordination artifact is needed.

Boundaries:
- Keep communication outputs draft-first unless a tool confirms the external action.
- Mark unclear owners or deadlines as unresolved instead of guessing.
- Respect read-only and write-boundary rules inherited from the current route.
